WEBVTT

00:03.237 --> 00:04.738
Previously on E.R.:

00:04.772 --> 00:06.340
If we're gonna do this,

00:06.374 --> 00:08.309
we're gonna have
to do this together.

00:08.342 --> 00:09.577
GATES:
Remembering a dream
I had last night.

00:09.610 --> 00:11.545
Sam was in it.
I don't beg.

00:11.579 --> 00:12.746
In my dream you did.

00:12.780 --> 00:14.482
This is Ortho.
Yeah, I start today.

00:14.515 --> 00:15.716
Dr. Rasgotra,
I'd like you to meet

00:15.749 --> 00:17.751
Drs. Ramsey, Craig...
Hey.

00:17.785 --> 00:19.387
Heard great
things about you.

00:19.420 --> 00:21.322
What position did you play?
Center forward.

00:21.355 --> 00:24.725
Love, trust, truth...
higher power.

00:24.758 --> 00:26.727
You can't have any
of those without faith

00:26.760 --> 00:27.795
Especially love.

00:27.828 --> 00:29.230
So this is your office?

00:29.263 --> 00:31.199
Mm-hmm.
(buttons scatter)

00:33.767 --> 00:35.035
Nice desk.

00:40.108 --> 00:43.677
Oh! Imagine waking up
here every morning.

00:43.711 --> 00:45.213
Betina, I can't afford this.

00:45.246 --> 00:48.116
Yes, you can.
I did the math.

00:48.149 --> 00:49.750
You did the math?

00:49.783 --> 00:52.720
Mm-hmm. Time to move out of
your med school apartment

00:52.753 --> 00:54.155
and invest in something.

00:54.188 --> 00:55.756
My apartment is fine.

00:55.789 --> 00:57.158
So what do you think?

00:57.191 --> 00:59.627
Oh, it's beautiful.
Told you.

00:59.660 --> 01:02.230
The sellers did a great
job on the renovation.

01:02.263 --> 01:04.432
The kitchen,
the moldings,

01:04.465 --> 01:06.300
these yummy floors.

01:06.334 --> 01:07.868
Bamboo flown in from Brazil.

01:07.901 --> 01:09.503
And there's a gym,

01:09.537 --> 01:11.572
and a children's game room
in the basement.

01:11.605 --> 01:12.740
Do you two have kids?

01:12.773 --> 01:14.142
No.
No.

01:14.175 --> 01:15.543
Listen,
don't rush it.

01:15.576 --> 01:17.478
When you're newlyweds
and it's just

01:17.511 --> 01:19.180
the two of you
against the world...

01:19.213 --> 01:21.549
Well, you can't beat it.

01:21.582 --> 01:23.651
Okay.

01:23.684 --> 01:25.353
It'll be gone by the end

01:25.386 --> 01:26.820
of the week, so if you're
at all interested,

01:26.854 --> 01:28.822
make an offer.

01:28.856 --> 01:30.224
No, thanks.

01:30.258 --> 01:31.792
It's, uh,

01:31.825 --> 01:33.327
the first place he's seen.

01:33.361 --> 01:34.528
Think about it.

01:34.562 --> 01:35.729
I'll call you tomorrow.

01:35.763 --> 01:38.166
No. Don't, please.

01:38.866 --> 01:41.169
I'm just looking.

01:42.370 --> 01:43.804
GATES:
Hey, Sam!

01:43.837 --> 01:45.839
It wasn't just the battery.

01:45.873 --> 01:47.375
Where did you
get my keys?

01:47.408 --> 01:48.842
You also had alternator issues.
You stole

01:48.876 --> 01:50.811
my keys and fixed my car?
I think

01:50.844 --> 01:52.613
the proper response would be,
"Thank you, Tony."

01:52.646 --> 01:54.248
Also, I tightened

01:54.282 --> 01:55.583
the connections and got you
all charged up.

01:55.616 --> 01:56.817
SKYE:
Ooh...

01:56.850 --> 01:58.452
That sounds like fun.

01:58.486 --> 01:59.820
I thought you were
dating the chaplain.

01:59.853 --> 02:01.755
It's my car.
He's talking about my car.

02:01.789 --> 02:03.724
Car.

02:03.757 --> 02:05.759
She made a perfectly
reasonable assumption
about our relationship

02:05.793 --> 02:07.228
and you practically
had a seizure.

02:07.261 --> 02:08.729
I wasn't feeling
the realtor.

02:08.762 --> 02:10.298
I just wanted to get out
of there, that's all.

02:10.330 --> 02:11.832
We're adults, Greg.
The topic of commitment

02:11.865 --> 02:13.834
shouldn't be off-limits.
It's not off limits.

02:13.867 --> 02:15.569
Really? You haven't
looked me in the eye

02:15.603 --> 02:17.938
since we left that place.
Come on, it's not like that.

02:17.971 --> 02:20.541
SKYE:
Pratt!

02:20.574 --> 02:23.644
Pratt, there's a kid and an
old guy that have just been

02:23.677 --> 02:25.279
pulled out of the lake.
Take one with Grady.

02:25.313 --> 02:26.747
All right, you got it.

02:26.780 --> 02:28.549
Look, let's just talk
about this later.

02:28.582 --> 02:30.384
At least you're admitting
there's something to talk about.

02:30.418 --> 02:31.852
Hey, Chaz, how are you doing?

02:31.885 --> 02:34.222
Fine. Thanks.
What up?

02:34.222 --> 02:35.589
Robert Truman, 68.

02:35.623 --> 02:37.425
Jumped in after a kid
who fell into the lake.

02:37.458 --> 02:39.727
Thought I could get him,
but I was too cold.

02:39.760 --> 02:41.229
Heart rate's 68,
pulse ox good.

02:41.229 --> 02:42.596
Temp was 90 when
we pulled him out.

02:42.630 --> 02:43.864
My lungs froze up,
couldn't swim.

02:43.897 --> 02:45.366
Does anything hurt, sir?

02:45.399 --> 02:47.235
I'm fine.
Take care of the boy.

02:47.268 --> 02:48.936
Barely moving air.
Too cold, can't get a sat.

02:48.969 --> 02:50.838
"24 gauge PIV."
That's it?

02:50.871 --> 02:51.805
He needs central access.

02:51.839 --> 02:53.507
Mama's here, it's okay.

02:53.541 --> 02:55.576
This is your fault!
You made this happen!

02:55.609 --> 02:58.546
No, he needed my help.
I thought that I...

02:58.579 --> 03:00.814
Why won't you leave us alone?
Ma'am, is he allergic

03:00.848 --> 03:02.916
to any medication?
No, I'm sorry I tried to come...

03:02.950 --> 03:04.318
Stay away from my son!

03:04.352 --> 03:05.553
SAM:
He's hypoventilating.

03:05.586 --> 03:06.954
SKYE:
We need to bag him.

03:06.987 --> 03:08.789
Doctor, please take care
of that child.

03:08.822 --> 03:10.658
Sir, we're going to
concentrate on you right now.

03:10.691 --> 03:12.926
No, if you want to help me,
you need to help that boy.

03:12.960 --> 03:14.795
Mr. Truman, please.
Save him!

03:14.828 --> 03:17.965
Save him or I'm going to hell.

